column7: Why I had a problem with Tyreek Hill's TD celebration. Next on @undisputed
Why I still like the Cowboys to win the NFC East (by default). Next on @undisputed
If only Dallas had an Ertz. Or a Dallas Goedert.
No way the Pats get back to the Super Bowl? Next on @undisputed
Tyson Chandler just got away with a goal-tend on Trae Young's last scoop shot.
Why I give Dak the bulk of the credit for last night's win at Philly. Next on @undisputed
If only Dak had an Ertz.

Shannon Sharpe says Belichick deserves 75% of the credit for the NE dynasty. Yet his defenses keep getting torched. Last yr's SBowl. At Jax. At Det. KC at home. And now 34 points to Tenn with 7 mins left.
How many times this season has Dak had to start inside his 10???
Why yesterday wasn’t Brady’s fault. And why Brees is now the NFL’s MVP. Next on @undisputed

Dak doesn't have much protection, hasn't had a receiver who can get open (pre-Amari), hasn't had a consistent run game or play calling ... and his confidence is crumbling. He's getting double-pumping hesitant and gunshy.

The defense coached by the genius Belichick has allowed 24 points in the 1st half at Tenn. At least the Cowboys allowed only 28 total. Brady has by far the highest degree of difficulty of any MVP candidate.
Shannon Sharpe is about to get an earful about my Cowboys. @undisputed. 9:30 AM ET. FS1
I tried to feed the fires of overconfidence in Philadelphia. The Eagles front-run, and right on schedule they fall on their faces. More @Undisputed, now on FS1 https://t.co/HSWboLM2UZ
Even scarier for Brady, Julian Edelman just doesn't have uncoverable burst he had before his knee injury.
I will be surprised if the Cowboys get 7 points out of this.
It will be virtually impossible for even Tom Brady to bring NE back from 24-10 down vs the defense that has allowed the NFL's fewest points this season - Tennessee's.
Brady caught THAT pass from Edelman but couldn't keep his balance after he turned to run. Still got 6 1/2 yards. He's only 41 years old.

Mariota often looks awkward throwing push passes. But every once in a while he makes a throw like he just made, a rainbow for a TD to Corey Davis beating Stephon Gilmore. Now I don't feel quite so bad about the Cowboys. Titans, 14-3.
Only hope now is a turnover.
Just one mistake.
Nobody open. But Dak has to throw that away.
Titans say, "Anything you can do, we can do better." Reverse pass to Mariota, who ran 4.5 at the combine. Somehow, I'll still take the QB who ran the ugliest combine 40 ever, the GOAT, Tom Brady.

No idea why Dak missed Zeke on first and goal. Awful pass? Not on same page? This offense is lucky to get ONE decent shot at getting it in the end zone and blew it. A win for Philly after the interception.

My school Vanderbilt keeps showing explosive bursts of offense (RB Ke'Shawn Vaughn has Kareem Hunt NFL capability) but again today, at Missouri, couldn't hold a commanding lead. But we're the Alabama of college football AS A SCHOOL AND A COLLEGE EXPERIENCE.
How does Shannon explain that LeBron James is the least clutch free throw shooter ever. Next on @undisputed
HE'S GOING TO THROW IT TO ERTZ ALMOST EVERY CRUCIAL TIME. DOUBLE HIM. FORCE WINCE TO GO ELSEWHERE.
LeBron, only 1 rebound, 1 assist at halftime as Lakers trail Hawks by 1. Mind must be on Cowboys-Eagles.
Eagles receivers make so many good grabs of wild throws.
THIS IS WAY TOO EASY. COME ON, DEFENSE, OFFENSE GAVE YOU SOME FRONT TO RUN WITH.
Wrong place, wrong time for the Cowboys. I just can't make any case for them this time. #FlyEaglesFly 34-10. FireJerryFire Jason Garrett.
Worth a try. I'll take an overthrow vs an underthrow.
He caught it.
Our "Ertz" from Stanford finally caught one and made a little play.
Jordan Matthews of Vanderbilt University should be catching passes from Tom Brady.

Unreal: The Cowboys go for it on 4th and short, as they should have, and Swaim flinches and false starts. That's a losing play by a 3-5 team ... which gives new life to Philly, which busts a big play. Just hard to watch.

Now I don't feel quite so bad about what Tennessee did on MNF to the Cowboys. But I still fear their confidence got crushed. I do not like their chances tonight at Eagles. I've lost faith in Garrett, Linehan, the O line, the D, Zeke's fitness and Dak in turning-point moments.
I like the QB draw call. Just great play by Cox.
The Cowboys continue to be so poorly coached. Another late play call. Run Dak on the read option!!!
I will not accept any "moral victory." In fact, that could be even worse big picture than getting blown out.
Obviously I was hoping the Cowboys could come out hot on offense and take it home. Instead, THAT happened. You're going to roll to Michael Bennett without blocking him???
LeBron must be furious the NBA is making him play the Hawks instead of letting him watch his Cowboys. He needs to speak to the commish about this.
That was just crushing. No pass rush. No run defense. Heath gets smoked. THAT WAS WHERE THE DEFENSE COULD'VE TAKEN A STAND AND TAKEN THE GAME OVER.
That's it. Kicker has gone south. Huge advantage, Philly. Eagles will be re-inspired. Psychological killer for Cowboys.
Now it feels like the Eagles are saying, OK, enough of this.

Without Gronk, Tom Brady's primary target has become Josh Gordon. Shannon Sharpe says Gordon now looks like he's running "with a piano on his back." On NE's opening drive, Gordon caught one big one, on 3rd and 10 ... and has already dropped two.
Mariota is shredding Belichick.
Amazing stand by the Cowboy defense. Hope it's not just your basic stay of execution.
Russell Wilson should've kept running with it. Looked like he pretty easily would've made the first down.
Let Dak run uptempo no-huddle as he did late first half vs Tenn. This is when he's best. Quits second-guessing. Just plants and fires.
Do I think the Cowboys can win at Atlanta and beat the Saints? NO. But do I feel way better about this team? YES. I'm going to bask in this for one whole week.
HOW BOUT THAT DAK PRESCOTT AND THAT EZEKIEL ELLIOTT! HOW BOUT THAT DEFENSE HOLDING AN OFFENSE WITH FOUR DANGEROUS RECEIVERS TO 20 POINTS AT PHILLY! HOW BOUT CARSON WINCE!
Matt Ryan will rally the Falcons. But how bout Baker Mayfield going 14 of 15 with 3 TDs as Cleveland leads Atl 21-10. I said Baker would be the best QB in this class and I stand by it.
Blitz. Force a quick throw. Tackle.

Lockett just caught the go-ahead TD pass and handed the ball to Floyd Mayweather, in the first row of the end zone. Floyd should be content to go to games, bask in his 50-0 glory, be honored by players who are in awe of him. No fighting "Uber drivers" in Japan.

As a Cowboy fan who hoped Wash would lose at TB, it just tears me up that the Bucs had 500 YARDS AND PUNTED JUST ONCE ... and scored only 3. Almost mathematically impossible. 4 turnovers and a missed chipshot FG. Gave me a headache.
I feel like I've already sweated out two games and we're just starting the second half.
That's when Dak is DAK (minus the sack). Just rock and fire. Throw it like he MEANS IT.
Guess the Saints are going to be OK without Dez. Up 45-7 at Cincy as they surge toward 8-1. Drew Brees is doing with only one real threat at WR, Michael Thomas, who is no speedster.
Luke Walton is ruining Lonzo Ball.

OU survives at home 48-47 when OKSt QB Cornelius finally throws a poor 2-pt pass for the win. OU finally fired defensive coordinator MStoops and it hasn't helped. OKSt: 640 yds, 501 passing, 39 1st downs. Just embarrassing. WVa might score 80 on OU at WVa.
If Zeke hadn't lost his balance after that incredible hurdle ...
Wonder if "Unc" has downed an extra bottle of Henny to drown the pain? Wonder if Shannon Sharpe, president of the National Cowboy Haters, will show up tomorrow at 9:30 E for Undisputed?
They just had to make this nervous.
WHAT A HURDLE BY ZEKE. UFNORTUNATELY LOST HIS BALANCE OR HE WOULD'VE SCORED. NOW IT WILL BE TOUGH. PLAY OF THE YEAR!
Rare good play call by Linehan.
LeBron James is the worst superstar late-game, close-game free throw shooter ever - his Achilles heel. Never seen anything like it.
Today's Undisputed podcast: https://t.co/AsfiWOjYyJ
PASS RUSH. TURNOVER.
Vander Esch made a terrific athletic play. But Jaylon Smith was flying in and would've made the tackle for a short gain at best.
Maybe they should use Jeff Heath on offense. What a pile-drive.
That was a vintage Dak/Zeke road drive for TD. HAVE I EVER MISSED THEM.

I love the Jimmy Butler trade for the Sixers. Now that Philly has 3 of the top 6 players in the East - including the East's best player, Joel Embiid, who made a stunningly clutch 19 of 22 FTs last night - I give the Sixers a very good shot at playing Golden State in the Finals.

LeBron just LeBricked TWO free throws, one for the win, next for the tie, then Kuzma rebounded and missed and LeBron follow-dunked for a one-point lead. Saved from the ultimate humiliation. 15 secs left.
At this rate, the Vander Esch interception return might end up being the best offensive play of the night.
I said before the season that Houston adding Melo would be subtraction by addition. I said Melo would make them worse. Sounds like he won't even last to Thanksgiving.
I despise the Philadelphia Eagles. That was as satisfyingly unexpected a win as I can ever remember. CryEaglesCry.

I was so wrong the day after the draft about Leighton Vander Esch. He's long, rangy, athletic and fast with terrific instincts and anticipation. He and Jaylon Smith could be attending Pro Bowls together at some point.
You can have Sam Darnold. I'm sticking with Baker Mayfield. Next on @undisputed
HOW BOUT THAT BAKER MAYFIELD LEADING THE BROWNS TO A 28-16 UPSET OF THE FALCONS (WITH LOTS OF HELP FROM HIS ROOKIE CAMP ROOMMATE NICK CHUBB).
Surprisingly, Tyson Chandler is changing the defensive mindset of the Lakers. The King's Team holding the Kings to only 86 in Sac was pretty impressive.
Is Dak a bust? @undisputed. 9:30 AM ET. FS1
Thank you to all who have served or are serving the Greatest Country in the World in our military. Never forget ... and you are not forgotten. We are forever grateful.

Dez unfortunately will find Achilles rehab is the longest and toughest of all injuries and sometimes the player just never gets his burst back. Dez will be tested like never before. The good news: He wasn't the quickest/fastest guy any way.

Sorry to hear about Dez's awful break. Achilles injuries are the most inexplicably mysterious in sports. They can rupture for no apparent reason while doing nothing risky. Often noncontact. I doubt it had anything to do with his extra weight or not being in football shape.

Every once in a while, there will just be a tour de force of firepower from Pittsburgh. Last night, we saw it from Big Ben and his weapons on offense. More @Undisputed, now on FS1 https://t.co/yfz2NT5Co1
Don't try to tell me Patrick Mahomes has run away with MVP. Next on @undisputed

Congrats, LeBron, the 4-6 Rockets just might be clearing a spot in the Western Conference playoffs for the Lakers. They just lost 98-80 to an OKC without Westbrook. They've lost their defensive identity and their offensive flow. They don't even look like a playoff team.
If this Steelers team, with this explosive offense and this pass rush, can't beat Tom Brady THIS time in Pittsburgh, on Dec. 16, the Steelers never will.

Also today: Will the Steelers win the AFC? Why would Belichick treat Brady like that? Why is Aaron Rodgers getting a pass for throwing so many passes away? Is Greek Freak that good or is Golden State in some trouble? @undisputed. 9:30 AM-Noon ET. FS1
Dez Bryant used to be the spirit of the Dallas Cowboys offense. But right now, as a Cowboys fan, I will take Amari Cooper over Dez. More @Undisputed, now on FS1 https://t.co/99IbBNGchN
Shannon and I debate why Floyd decided not to fight the "Uber driver." Next on @undisputed
LeBron, you have to initiate the offense and just close the deal. These are the Timberwolves. This is not Golden State. This is not Houston. More @Undisputed, now on FS1 https://t.co/78sy5jgYU9
